<%- include("../partials/header") %>
<%- include("../partials/sidebar") %>

<main id="page-content" class="container-fluid fadeIn">
  <div class="container-fluid">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-lg-2 col-md-12 col-sm-12 m-1">
        <%- include("../partials/menu") %>
      </div>

      <div class="col-lg-8 col-md-12 col-sm-12 m-1">
        <header class="jumbotron">
          <h1 class="display-3 ml-5">Welcome!</h1>
          <pre>
              This WebApp is made with NodeJS (and all main modules - like Express and Passport), REST, Boostrap, jQuery
          and some basic HTML, CSS and JS scripts. App is using middlewares for user verification and some alerts
          (you can test it in 'Sign Up' form and then 'Add New Page').

          There are also some games and quick tools you can check in menu or 'Landing Page'
          (I recommend to check the 'Keyboard Drums').

          Whole thing is in docker container connected to MongoDB and deployed in docker-compose on my personal home server.

              I hope You enjoy it, cheers :)
            </pre>
          <hr class="my-4">
          <p>
            <a class="btn btn-secondary btn-lg ml-5" href="/pages/new">Add New Page Â»</a>
          </p>
        </header>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="container-fluid">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-lg-2 col-md-2 hidden-sm">
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-10 col-md-10 col-sm-12">
        <% pages.forEach(function(page){ %>
        <a href="/pages/<%= page._id %>">
          <figure class="col-md-4">
            <img class="img-fluid img-shadow img-animation" src="<%= page.image %>">
          </figure>
        </a>
        <% }); %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</main>

<%- include ("../partials/footer") %>
